<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Kromnik</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2004<br />
	Location: California
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>To my knowledge it's spread out equally, based upon the level of the player that dies among the group.  A higher level player may not get the same amount as a lower player, though, because the amount of death debt lost at a lower player's level is probably less for them.  <br />
<br />
I don't think it has anything to do with who goes down first.  If it's one death, it's probably based on the penalty for that level, spread among the group.  If it's several, it's probably the averaged based upon the dead players' levels.  Again, the higher player may receive less penalty.  <br />
<br />
You may think that it's unfair, but consider if the group breaks up...you go out and kill 10 blue mobs solo to make up for the debt.  The same mobs could be grey to the higher player, so they shouldn't have to kill  10 blue mobs of a level that could be orange or red to you, which is something you may not be able to do.  That wouldn't be fair either.  Maybe they have to kill 5 blue to him and orange/red to you mobs to make up for theirs.  Works out about the same, in terms of difficulty.<br />
<br />
At least this is how I understand it.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
