	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Gojirax</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>It does matter.<br />
<br />
When the first person dies, you all share 1/6 of the debt. But if that first person releases to their bind point, then they won't share in the loss of all the rest.<br />
<br />
If everyone releases when they die, then the last man standing will eat all 5 of the previous people's deaths and SOLO his own Xp debt.<br />
<br />
He will have easily a half yellow bubble more debt more than the first person that died.<br />
<br />
It's really bad form to release when your group is wiping, unless you are near the bind point and can come try to help. (Plus, if you are in the same zone when you die and are nearby, you will still share in the debt.)</p>
	
	
	
