	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>*Shrug* I like the fact that there's a system that forces people to pay attention to what they're doing. I wasn't too keen on the idea from the outset, but they've got it tuned where it isn't a huge issue. If another group member dies, you're looking at around 2-3% of XP debt if they get a rez or recover their shard. That's made up in 3 or 4 group kills. Again, it's very minimal, but it's enough so that it will make people do their best to keep group mates alive, because it can stack up on you if you're not doing your job.<br />
<br />
I've had maybe 1 or 2 groups so far in both beta and retail where I've left with more than a few percentage points of XP debt. <br />
<br />
-Tok</p>
	
	
	
