	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Harvyst</b><br /><i>It does make the learning curve tough on others though.<br />
<br />
I've been trying to teach some of my friend tactics regarding aggro and crowd control. Some of them are a bit dense. The xp debt problem is very frustrating and means sometimes I just don't have the patience to sit and babysit them while they figure out that nuking every 2 seconds is going to attract the mob's attention away from the tank...</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>True and I'm seeing the newer players having to climb that curve more now that the game has been out a few weeks.  Also, what debt does is make people scared of it and once incurred, obsessed with getting the shard back.  However, the same happened in EQ1 regarding lost xp.  Many players would die and then spend over an hour trying to get a 96% rez when they could have just taken a lower level rez and gotten the xp back in just a few minutes.<br />
<br />
I'm finding I just have to be more careful with who I group with and feel very lucky to have a regular duo partner.  The game is still fairly new though and hopefully a lot of players will be through the curve soon. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>WhoMe</b><br /><i>1. And this happened to me. Party in Stormhold, full group we wipe due to a bad pull. When u release u end up outside stormhold, ok np zone back in ........ummm I am in but group is still grayed out. Oh they are in Stormhold2 I am in stormhold3. Cant reach group so can't get any debt payed back, suck up 113% debt have a nice day. And I thought this game was beta tested? I myself hope they fix this one or else your on your own in some zones.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>EQ2 needs some more work whenever instanced zones, shards, and groups are involved.  However, your particular problem could have been solved if your group had zoned out and everyone met up outside of Stormhold, for example.  I had that same problem except one of the group members shards had been merged into another one of the instances!  Luckily it was fairly crowded so CR was very easy.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>WhoMe</b><br /><i>2. The debt system only makes it so u won't deding you are still losing exp, but I agree its better then dedinging.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I don't really care much about losing a level.  If you had happened to lose a level, you should still be so close to getting it back that a few minutes of xp will ding you.  We'll have to see how this works out later in the game though with raids and higher level dungeons.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>WhoMe</b><br /><i>3. It seams if you are the last to die you get more debt then the rest of the group, my be wrong on that but I asked rest of group what there debt was and seemed to be diff for each member even tho we where all same level.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Totally!  This has to be a bug and has been brought up a few times on Sony's EQ2 boards.  Not only does the last to die (or be rezzed / revive, forget which) but the shared debt is not calculating correctly either.  Any time my group has wiped I have ended up with a lot more than 2.5% debt.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>WhoMe</b><br /><i>4. Last night got group died np got shard back had 4% debt, killed 5 mobs all white con got down to 1% or what should have been 1% but now my debt went up ?????? Check with group Mmmmm same thing , killed mobs got back down to 1% then it took 3 times what I killed to get 3% back just to get the 1% back and get even, all white cons all the same mobs. I think the system has a lot of bugs still and needs lots of work still. </i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I have noticed this too, never more than 1% though.  It seems that when debt is calculated it really doesn't like to take tenths into the equation (rounding up) until you reach your debt %, then it decides to round up, appearing as though you have more debt.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>WhoMe</b><br /><i>I myself like things about both systems but if they ever get it working like it should it would be ok</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>The system should work very well and add the same risk / reward for dangerous encounters, but not the stupidly difficult task of CR'ing without gear in such a dangerous encounter.  There has to be some kind of risk and a smoothly running debt system looks like a good solution.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Toktuk Wartalon</b><br /><i>I believe your shard remains in the instance you died in. That's why you can't recover shards from personal instances simply by creating a new instance zone. If you died in instance 2 and then zoned into instance 3, I don't believe you would have found a shard.<br />
<br />
-Tok</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I have seen a players shard be moved to another zone instance, and it's really annoying! <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" />  My experience was as follows (involves a combination of grouping, instanced zones, and shards):<br />
<br />
Group of 6 in Blackburrow2.  When we zoned in we all got into Blackburrow2 and were the only ones in the zone.  Blackburrow1 had close to 30 people in it.  We had a tough fight with a few pops that added and ended up losing a couple group members.  One of them ended up reviving thinking we had wiped, when we did end up making it through the encounter with a few group members left.  When the revived group member got back to Blackburrow she could not get into Blackburrow2 any longer, so zoned into Blackburrow1 to find she had a corpse trail.  She tried several times to get back into Blackburrow2 so some of the group zoned out, only to find the same problem - no Blackburrow2.  We all zoned out, back into Blackburrow1, got her shard and went about xping in Blackburrow1.<br />
<br />
Instances should remain available as long as there is a single player in it, *especially* if you are grouped with players in an inaccessable instance!<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Sudedor</b><br /><i>You can recover a shard in any instance of the zone.<br />
<br />
For instance, we had someone die in BB3 the other night (late) where we were the only ones in the zone.  The rest of us made a run for the exit and made it out.  We zoned back in and BB3 had closed, gone.  Still got the shard in BB1.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Yup, it seems as though shards can be assimilated into other instances.</p>
	
	
	
