<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Sudedor</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Oracle<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2004<br />
	Location: North Carolina, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Actually I don't think that part is working as intended.  I think that the debt should be equally shared regardless of release or not.  I believe that was how it was intended.<br />
<br />
My "guess" on how this slid by was that most of the "dumping" is happening when people die, release and the release removes them from the zone.  Since they are not in the zone, they don't share in the subsequent debt that accrues.<br />
<br />
For instance, a party of 6 in Stormhold, the last person to die will accrue HUGE debt if the previous 5 all release at death, since the nearest revive is in Antonica.<br />
<br />
I think that's a bug, and I'm going to bug it every time I log on and every time I die until it's fixed.  I encourage you to do the same.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
