	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Gojirax</b><br /><i>I also think the shared Exp debt thing is working as intended.<br />
<br />
All in all, it's a decent system, you just need to group with people that won't release and dump debt on people.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>That's the problem though, there shouldn't be an option.  If the debt system were working as intended then the last person to die in a group wipe wouldn't share the debt for all the previous deaths while the first person to die doesn't.  I'm not sure exactly how it works with releasing and the order in which you die, but I do know that the more deaths prior to your own the more debt you will share, regardless of whether other members release or not.<br />
<br />
Last night I was with my duo partner and zoned into a white^^ in crypt...of something...(off of Vernin Snye) <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" />  Anyway, it ended up being too much for us, especially since we got jumped but we really tried.  She ended up dying *just* before she zoned (shakes fist at having to click on the instanced zone you want to go to hehe) but I was already zoning when she died.  I did not share any of her debt and she did not release.  I revived her and still did not share any debt.<br />
<br />
That's not working as intended.</p>
	
	
	
