<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Thyramon</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Dec 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>There is one other thing that people haven't pointed out about xp debt in EQ2:<br />
<br />
<b>It goes away on its own over time.</b><br />
<br />
I know this for a fact.  I was having a bad night with some friends, group mobs that we usually kill without much effort were kicking our rears all over antonica.  In the span of about 3 hours we racked up over 2.5 yellows (25%) xp debt each.  We got fed up, called it a night and logged out.  I logged back in the next morning (about 6-8 hours-ish later) to find my staggering 25% xp debt had dwindled to 1% while I slept.<br />
<br />
A bad day can be completely countered by taking a break and doing something else: sleeping, watching some tv, playing an alt, tradeskilling, etc.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Thyrsham Foehammer - Venerable Barbarian Prophet of the Tribunal<br />
Thyran - 14 Shaman/11 Scholar<br />
Thyranus - 17 Brawler<br />
